# Build artifacts
# NOTE: this must be anchored to the repo root (leading slash) - a bare
# "langstream" pattern matches *any* file or directory named "langstream"
# at any depth in Git's gitignore semantics, which silently swallowed the
# entire pkg/langstream/ and cmd/langstream/ packages on the first push
# (2026-07-07). Anchoring to root fixes that while still ignoring the
# compiled binary `go build ./cmd/langstream` drops in the repo root.
/bin/
/langstream
*.exe

# Go
*.test
*.out

# Stray zero-byte temp files left behind by gofmt -w on some sandboxed/
# bindfs-mounted filesystems (rename-based atomic write falls back to a
# temp file the OS won't let us unlink there). Harmless - never matched by
# the Go toolchain since they don't end in exactly ".go" - but keep them
# out of git.
*.go.[0-9]*

# OS/editor cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp
